text: Zdeněk Jičínský (26 February 1929 – 9 April 2020) was a Czech lawyer and politician. He served as a member of the Chamber of Deputies of the Czech Republic from 1996 to 2002 and from 2003 to 2010. He was also a member of the Federal Assembly of Czechoslovakia (1969, 1990–92). He was born in Ostřešany. Jičínský died on 9 April 2020 at the age of 91. ==References== Category:1929 births Category:2020 deaths Category:Czech politicians Category:European lawyers Category:Pardubice Region
